n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interstate_476"}
{"title_page": "Bitter Tears (song)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Bitter Tears\n| cover      = BitterTears.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[INXS]]\n| album      = [[X (INXS album)|X]]\n| released   = {{flagicon|AUS}}February 1991 <br>{{flagicon|UK}}July 1991\n| format     = [[7\"]], [[12\"]], [[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 1990\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Alternative rock]]\n| length     = 3:49\n| label      = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| writer     = [[Michael Hutchence]], [[Andrew Farriss]]\n| producer   = [[Chris Thomas (record producer)|Chris Thomas]]\n| prev_title = [[By My Side (INXS song)|By My Side]]\n| prev_year  = 1991\n| next_title = [[The Stairs (song)|The Stairs]]\n| next_year  = 1991\n}}\n\n\"'''Bitter Tears'''\" is a single by [[INXS]], the third Australian and fourth UK single taken from their album ''[[X (INXS album)|X]]''. It peaked at #30 on the [[UK Singles Chart]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.everyhit.com |title=UK Top 40 Chart Archive, British Singles & Album Charts |publisher=everyHit.com |date=2000-03-16 |accessdate=2012-01-16}}</ref> improving on the disappointing performance of the previous single, \"[[By My Side (INXS song)|By My Side]]\".  The single was released to coincide with the band headlining the SummerXS concert at Wembley Stadium in July 1991, as documented in the [[Live Baby Live (DVD)|Live Baby Live DVD]].\n\nThe song was written by [[Andrew Farriss]] and [[Michael Hutchence]] as part of the sessions for the ''X'' album.\n\n==B-sides==\nThe B-sides are a live version of \"Faith In Each Other\" from the ''X'' album, \"The Other Side\", written and performed by guitarist & saxophonist [[Kirk Pengilly]] and \"Soothe Me\" written and performed by guitarist & keyboard player [[Andrew Farriss]].\n\n==Track listing==\n;UK 7\"\n#\"Bitter Tears\" (LP Version)\n#\"Soothe Me\"\n#\"Bitter Tears\" (Lorimer 7\" Edit)\n\n;UK 12\" Single\n#\"Bitter Tears\" (12\" Lorimer Remix)\n#\"Disappear\" (Morales Remix)\n#\"Tears Are Bitter\" (Instrumental Club Mix)\n\n;UK 12\" Special Edition (Wembley Stadium Cover)\n#\"Bitter Tears\" (Lorimer 12\" Mix)\n#\"Disappear (Morales 12\" Mix)\n#\"Soothe Me\"\n\n;UK CDS\n#\"Bitter Tears\"\n#\"Soothe Me\"\n#\"Original Sin\"\n#\"Listen Like Thieves\" - Extended Remix\n\n;US Maxi CD\n#\"Bitter Tears\" (LP Version)\n#\"Bitter Tears\" (12\" Lorimer Remix)\n#\"Bitter Tears\" (Instrumental)\n#\"Disappear\" (Morales Remix)\n#\"The Other Side\"\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1991)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n|Australian [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Singles Chart]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|36\n|-\n|[[UK Singles Chart]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|30\n|-\n|U.S. [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|46\n|-\n|U.S. ''Billboard'' [[Mainstream Rock Tracks]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4\n|-\n|U.S. ''Billboard'' [[Modern Rock Tracks]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|}\n\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1991)\n!Position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Canada Top Singles (''RPM'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.2024&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.2024.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.2024|title=RPM 100 Hit Tracks of 1991|work=RPM|accessdate=November 23, 2017}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|99\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{INXS}}\n\n[[Category:INXS songs]]\n[[Category:1991 singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Andrew Farriss]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Michael Hutchence]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Chris Thomas (record producer)]]\n[[Category:1990 songs]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records singles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Bitter Tears\n| cover      = BitterTears.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[INXS]]\n| album      = [[X (INXS album)|X]]\n| released   = {{flagicon|AUS}}February 1991 <br>{{flagicon|UK}}July 1991\n| format     = [[7\"]], [[12\"]], [[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 1990\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Alternative rock]]\n| length     = 3:49\n| label      = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| writer     = [[Michael Hutchence]], [[Andrew Farriss]]\n| producer   = [[Chris Thomas (record producer)|Chris Thomas]]\n| prev_title = [[By My Side (INXS song)|By My Side]]\n| prev_year  = 1991\n| next_title = [[The Stairs (song)|The Stairs]]\n| next_year  = 1991\n}}\n\n\"'''Bitter Tears'''\" is a single by [[INXS]], the third Australian and fourth UK single taken from their album ''[[X (INXS album)|X]]''. It peaked at #30 on the [[UK Singles Chart]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.everyhit.com |title=UK Top 40 Chart Archive, British Singles & Album Charts |publisher=everyHit.com |date=2000-03-16 |accessdate=2012-01-16}}</ref> improving on the disappointing performance of the previous single, \"[[By My Side (INXS song)|By My Side]]\".  The single was released to coincide with the band headlining the SummerXS concert at Wembley Stadium in July 1991, as documented in the [[Live Baby Live (DVD)|Live Baby Live DVD]].\n\nThe song was written by [[Andrew Farriss]] and [[Michael Hutchence]] as part of the sessions for the ''X'' album.\n\n==B-sides==\nThe B-sides are a live version of \"Faith In Each Other\" from the ''X'' album, \"The Other Side\", written and performed by guitarist & saxophonist [[Kirk Pengilly]] and \"Soothe Me\" written and performed by guitarist & keyboard player [[Andrew Farriss]].\n\n==Track listing==\n;UK 7\"\n#\"Bitter Tears\" (LP Version)\n#\"Soothe Me\"\n#\"Bitter Tears\" (Lorimer 7\" Edit)\n\n;UK 12\" Single\n#\"Bitter Tears\" (12\" Lorimer Remix)\n#\"